{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QPpzoVUf1UwWUejdhP3SKD","type":"tool_result","content":"  2270→- **8 consecutive sessions wasted on the same one-line bug.** This is the defining failure of the day's second half. A guard `if (current === 'done') return` in the reconciliation logic would have prevented all 8 sessions.\n  2271→- **Action items from retros are completely ignored.** \"Fix state reconciliation\" has been logged as CRITICAL in every retro since session 9. It has never been implemented. The retro system produces action items that nobody reads or acts on.\n  2272→- **Ralph has no sprint-complete exit.** An autonomous agent that keeps running on a finished sprint is burning tokens in an infinite loop. This was flagged in session 9. Still unfixed.\n  2273→- **Data fixes instead of code fixes — still.** Session after session edits sprint-state.json to fix symptoms. The code that causes the corruption remains untouched.\n  2274→- **No escalation mechanism.** There is no way for the system to detect \"I have fixed this same problem 8 times\" and stop, alert the user, or refuse to proceed.\n  2275→\n  2276→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  2277→\n  2278→1. **Retros without enforcement are documentation, not process improvement.** This is the 8th retro to identify the same bug. The action item system has zero enforcement. Writing \"CRITICAL\" in a markdown table does nothing if no agent or human reads it before the next session.\n  2279→\n  2280→2. **State reconciliation must be proof-document-aware.** The reconciliation logic must check whether a proof document exists in git before downgrading a story's status. If `verification/{story}-proof.md` exists and is committed, the story is `done` regardless of what any other signal says.\n  2281→\n  2282→3. **`done` is terminal. Period.** No reconciliation logic, no state migration, no session-start hook should ever transition a story OUT of `done` status. This is the single most important invariant in the sprint state machine.\n  2283→\n  2284→4. **Autonomous agents need hard termination conditions.** Ralph must check `sprint.done === sprint.total` before launching a session. If true, it should log \"sprint complete, nothing to do\" and exit immediately — no reconciliation, no story selection, no retro.\n  2285→\n  2286→5. **The cost of inaction compounds non-linearly.** Session 9 identified this as a one-line fix. 8 sessions later, the total waste is $80-120+. Every additional session ralph launches will add another $5-10 of pure waste.\n  2287→\n  2288→## 7. Action Items\n  2289→\n  2290→| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n  2291→|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n  2292→| 1 | **Fix state reconciliation to treat `done` as terminal** — add guard: `if (current === 'done') return`. | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN — **unfixed for 8 consecutive sessions (9-16). One-line fix.** |\n  2293→| 2 | **Stop ralph immediately** — the sprint is complete, ralph is generating an infinite loop of waste sessions | CRITICAL | User | NEW — **do this NOW** |\n  2294→| 3 | **Add ralph sprint-complete termination** — refuse to launch sessions when `sprint.done === sprint.total` | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN — **unfixed since session 9** |\n  2295→| 4 | **Make reconciliation proof-document-aware** — check git for proof docs before modifying story status | HIGH | Infrastructure | OPEN — **carried from session 13** |\n  2296→| 5 | **Add circuit breaker for repeated identical fixes** — detect N identical state corruptions and halt | HIGH | Infrastructure | OPEN — **carried from session 15** |\n  2297→| 6 | **Convert retro action items to stories** — action items that survive 8+ retros are a process failure | HIGH | Process | OPEN — **carried from session 13** |\n  2298→| 7 | **Reduce \"unknown\" story cost bucket** — $124.43 (19.5%) unattributed cost | LOW | Tooling | OPEN — carried forward |\n  2299→| 8 | **Plan next sprint** — all 17 epics complete. Action items 1, 3-6 above should be the first stories. | HIGH | PM | OPEN — carried forward |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013quVZapex2pGR1yUvDBNko","session_id":"90decdda-ba60-48f6-a288-f3c67f5017cd","uuid":"489fe694-7d17-476d-b5d9-4bfafab76986","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:44:40.034Z"}
